# Visual Design Standards

## Spacing — Base-8 System

Never use arbitrary values. Every spacing decision from this scale:

- 4px — micro (icon padding, badge offset)
- 8px — tight (related inline elements)
- 12px — compact (dense list items)
- 16px — default (standard padding, related elements)
- 24px — comfortable (section padding, grouped elements)
- 32px — loose (section separation)
- 48px — spacious (major section breaks)
- 64px — generous (page-level breathing room)

Related items: 8-16px. Grouped sections: 24-32px. Unrelated sections: 48px+. Never 13px, 22px, 37px, or any off-scale value.

Whitespace is not empty space — it creates focus, breathing room, and elegance. Crowded UIs feel cheap.

## Typography

**Scale:** 12px (captions) / 14px (labels) / 16px (body) / 18px (subheadings) / 24px (section headings) / 32px (page titles)

**Line length:** 45-75 characters optimal. Mobile: 35-50 acceptable.
**Line height:** Body 1.5x, headings 1.2x, captions 1.4x.
**Weights:** Max 3 per product: regular (400), medium (500), semibold (600).
**Letter spacing:** 0 for body. +0.05em for ALL CAPS labels. Slightly negative for display headings.
**Rules:** Max 2 typefaces. Size + weight + color creates hierarchy — never change all three simultaneously.

## Color System

**Architecture:** Brand (2-3), Neutrals (5-7), Semantic (4: green/yellow/red/blue), Surfaces (3-4).

**60-30-10 Rule:** 60% dominant neutral, 30% secondary, 10% accent/brand.

**Rules:**
- Never use color as the only differentiator (8% of men are colorblind)
- Always pair: color + icon, color + label
- Red = error/danger only, never just "important"
- Contrast: 4.5:1 normal text, 3:1 large text (WCAG 2.1)
- Dark mode: redesign, don't invert. Use #121212 base, reduce saturation, elevate with lighter surfaces not shadows.

## Iconography

**Sizes:** 16px (info), 20px (inline action), 24px (standalone), 32px (empty states).
**Touch target:** Always 44x44px minimum regardless of visual size.
**Consistency:** Never mix outline, filled, and duotone on same screen.
**Labels:** Icons alone only for universal symbols (close, search, back). Otherwise always icon + label.
**Color:** Decorative = text color. Status = semantic color. Interactive = primary color. Disabled = 40% opacity.

## The Grid

- Mobile: 4 columns, 16px gutters, 16px margins
- Tablet: 8 columns, 16px gutters, 24px margins
- Desktop: 12 columns, 24px gutters, 32-64px margins
- All text on baseline grid (4px or 8px multiples)
- Break the grid only intentionally and rarely — one break creates emphasis, everything breaking creates chaos
